defaultThe relationship between sustainability and agricultural production is sometimes referred to as a balance or trade-off
default: there is an assumption that actions taken to improve environmental performance decrease production and 
defaultvice versa
default.  Sometimes this is the case, but often production is only increased in the short term or requires significant additional inputs.  Integrate
defaultd actions resulting in win-win outcomes are possible, enhancing both farming’s sustainability and its productivity.  In addition, the services provided by the natural environment are vital to production.  Sustainability, by definition, is a necessary pre-r
defaultequisite of ongoing agricultural productivity.
default Evidence demonstrates that the l
defaultonger-term sustainability of food production 
defaultis inherently linked to the 
defaultintegration of environmental 
defaultand agronomic 
defaultpriorities
default. 
